==English==

===Etymology===
Coined between 1820 and 1830 from {{L.}} ''[[aberrans]]'', ''-rantis'', present participle of ''[[aberrare]]''.<ref>[http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/aberrant Aberrant at Dictionary.com]</ref> See [[aberr]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/əˈbɛrənt, ˈæbər-/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Wandering; [[straying]] from the right way.
# {{biology}} [[deviating|Deviating]] from the ordinary or natural type; [[exceptional]]; [[abnormal]].
#* [[w:Charles Darwin|Charles Darwin]],
#*: The more '''aberrant''' any form is, the greater must have been the number of connecting forms which, on my theory, have been exterminated.
# Deviating from [[morality]].

